</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Species in this genus are mainly associated with plants in the family 
<taxonomicName genus="Asclepiadaceae" lsidName="Asclepiadaceae" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="genus">Asclepiadaceae</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
